# ── Stock-GEX dedicated Skylit session (session B) ────────────────────────
# The live index tracker (terminal 1) and the Railway app share ONE Skylit
# session via Postgres. Skylit's __client cookie ROTATES on every JWT refresh
# (auth.js:170), so a 2nd process refreshing the SAME session clobbers it and
# both die. The stock-gex tools (terminal 2) therefore need their OWN session.
#
# SETUP:
#   1. Log into app.skylit.ai in a SEPARATE browser (incognito / another
#      profile) so you get a distinct Clerk session.
#   2. DevTools → Application → Cookies → app.skylit.ai:
#        __client        → CLERK_CLIENT_COOKIE
#        __client_uat    → CLERK_CLIENT_UAT
#      Network → any clerk.skylit.ai/v1/client/sessions/<SID>/tokens request:
#        the <SID> in the URL → CLERK_SESSION_ID
#   3. Paste below, save as  session-b.env  (NOT .example — that name is gitignored).
#
# DATABASE_URL is deliberately EMPTY: it forces initAuth off Postgres (so this
# process never touches session A) and onto these .env creds = session B.
# UNUSUAL_WHALES_API_KEY is NOT set here — it's inherited from root .env (only
# keys present in this file override; everything else falls through).

CLERK_SESSION_ID=sess_REPLACE_ME
CLERK_CLIENT_COOKIE=REPLACE_ME
CLERK_CLIENT_UAT=REPLACE_ME
DATABASE_URL=
